
[1]burgage

   BURG'AGE, n. [from burg.] In English law, tenure in burgage, or burgage
   tenure, is tenure in socage, applied to cities or towns, or where
   houses, or lands which were formerly the site of houses, in an ancient
   borough, are held of some lord in common socage by a certain
   established rent; a remnant of Saxon liberty.
